dct_title_s: Eastern Turkey in Asia. Samawa, sheet 41. Series G.S.G.S. no. 1522a
dct_description_sm: "Drawn at the Ordinance Survey Office, Southampton, 1915. Printed at the War Office, Jany. 1915." Relief shown by form lines and by spot heights. Includes an index to adjoining sheets, and a glossary. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. no. 1522a. Relief shown by form lines and spot heights. Some sheets from this set were issued by War Office. Intelligence Division I.D.W.O. no. 1522. Series covers Mesopotamia and eastern Anatolian parts of Ottoman Empire. "Compiled for the Geographical Section, General Staff by Lieut. Colonel F.R. Maunsell, C.M.G. [from] Surveys in Lower Mesopotamia by Sir W. Willcocks, 1909-11, Journey in N.E. Arabia by Capt. G. Leachman, Royal Sussex Regt. 1910, Am Euphrat und Tigris by E. Sachau, 1897-8." With glossary. Set complete, see index. Shows lines of ancient canals. Great Britain. War Office. Intelligence Division I.D.W.O. no. 1522.
dct_creator_sm: Great Britain. War Office. Intelligence Division
